E3MjYyMzU5ODAsImlhdCI6MTcyMzY0Mzk4MCwiaXNzIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9hcGkucGFzc3BvcnQub=
25saW5lL29hdXRoIiwic2NvcGUiOiJmZWVkOnJlYWQgYXJ0aWNsZTpyZWFkIGFzc2V0OnJlYWQg=
Y2F0ZWdvcnk6cmVhZCBlbnRpdGxlbWVudHMiLCJzdWIiOiJXUkNYVjdONVZWc1paemVuYkVnN0h=
FIiwidXNlIjoiYWNjZXNzIn0.qdIofEtcog66Kqtbi3mSx0hG4UGj_v38sRzDnPkvNgo9AImgrW=
W2w7bFAst9d59DqcC2lB8ufKYjTB2ZuB8ySINhxDU-u6CIYz80sbod33DcQ3cpY6qjlKRoJ4iDC=
Mqup73S2KOHebx0xeSJ6CRmvtZ4CRY3Wi26Fi3OjWprLVmKoKSgYxwdY7AsQk8rlmanu3esiHCu=
x5HovFUe8nidR9TbMNXMbtGDPfZkm92hRNlzPARwL1XaVHsR6_qgn0BBckswhbzbn0DKHeabGTf=
pkk_M-_T-WubJf9EI_x7k3yL0Gjk2XNQ3Q3CHh2UGzi4nO66091OjuBpFprIRQujQcw ) :

Google has a very long ways to go to make [Google=E2=80=99s True Moonshot] =
a reality, or, frankly, to even make it a corporate goal. It will cost a lo=
t of money, risk partnerships, and lower margins. It is, though, a massive =
opportunity =E2=80=94 the maximal application of AI to Google=E2=80=99s bus=
iness prospects =E2=80=94 and it strikes me as a pretty big deal that, at l=
east when it comes to the org chart, the Pixel has been elevated above Andr=
oid.

In fact, though, my takeaway from yesterday=E2=80=99s event is the opposite=
: Android still matters most, and the integration Google is truly betting o=
n is with the cloud.

The Pixel Angle
---------------

That=E2=80=99s not to say that Google is giving up on integration completel=
y; President of Android Ecosystem Sameer Samat framed Google=E2=80=99s appr=
oach this way:

( https://videopress.com/embed/MUONjGC2?hd=3D1&cover=3D1&loop=3D0&autoPlay=
=3D0&permalink=3D1&muted=3D0&controls=3D1&playsinline=3D0&useAverageColor=
=3D0&preloadContent=3Dmetadata )

As Rick said earlier, this is where our decades of investment in AI and Goo=
gle=E2=80=99s full tech stack make Gemini really special. Gemini can handle=
 these kinds of complex personal queries within Google=E2=80=99s own secure=
 cloud, without sending any of your personal data to a third-party AI provi=
der you may not know or trust. And for some of the most sensitive use cases=
, like summarizing audio from a phone call, or suggesting a helpful reply t=
o an encrypted text message, we=E2=80=99ve pioneered on-device generative A=
I with Gemini Nano. It=E2=80=99s the first time a large multimodal AI model=
 has been optimized for a mobile device, so the data never leaves your phon=
e. With Gemini deeply integrated with Android, we=E2=80=99re well on our wa=
y to rebuilding the OS with AI at the core. The new Gemini assistant brings=
 the benefits of AI to billions around the world, while helping to keep you=
r personal information secure and private. Android is truly leading the way=
 towards AI for everyone.

To the extent Google is betting on Pixel, it=E2=80=99s that the company wil=
l deliver on this hybrid approach more effectively than anyone else in the =
ecosystem, and that=E2=80=99s not nothing: Google has ultimate control of a=
 Pixel device, and can reap all of the benefits of integration I highlighte=
d above.

In the end, though, Google=E2=80=99s real bet is that owning the informatio=
n stack matters more than owning the tech stack, particularly when you have=
 the most capable cloud infrastructure to act on it. That is, of course, th=
e same Android strategy as always; the bet is that AI does the hard work of=
 making it more attractive to premium customers than it has to date.

Integration, Innovation, and the DOJ
------------------------------------

From Bloomberg ( https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-08-13/doj-con=
siders-seeking-google-goog-breakup-after-major-antitrust-win ) :

A bid to break up Alphabet Inc.=E2=80=99s Google is one of the options bein=
g considered by the Justice Department after a landmark court ruling found =
that the company monopolized the online search market, according to people =
with knowledge of the deliberations.

The move would be Washington=E2=80=99s first push to dismantle a company fo=
r illegal monopolization since unsuccessful efforts to break up Microsoft C=
orp. two decades ago. Less severe options include forcing Google to share m=
ore data with competitors and measures to prevent it from gaining an unfair=
 advantage in AI products, said the people, who asked not to be identified =
discussing private conversations.

Regardless, the government will likely seek a ban on the type of exclusive =
contracts that were at the center of its case against Google. If the Justic=
e Department pushes ahead with a breakup plan, the most likely units for di=
vestment are the Android operating system and Google=E2=80=99s web browser =
Chrome, said the people. Officials are also looking at trying to force a po=
ssible sale of AdWords, the platform the company uses to sell text advertis=
ing, one of the people said.

