 handling AI related to your personal data that is held on the device they =
sell, and they are really the only ones that can do so; =E2=80=9Cworld know=
ledge=E2=80=9D is being handled by OpenAI for now, but the company has been=
 clear that there will be other offerings.

What Google is proposing is something different entirely: you can pick your=
 device, but your AI will be integrated with your data primarily via the cl=
oud; the company can pull that off because they own both Android and the cl=
oud. It=E2=80=99s something different and, to the extent the DOJ is concern=
ed with historial patterns of innovation, they should let Google=E2=80=99s =
integration be.

